title: The Edmonton Oilers Cup Run of 2006 - Western SF vs The Sharks
description:
With the first seeded Red Wings out of the way, the next foe to be shot in the mouth were the San Jose Sharks. The dynamic duo of Joe Thornton and Jonathan Chechoo were the main dangermen, but it was the Sharks&#039; defence that prevailed early on.

Many doubted the Oilers&#039; chances after digging themselves a hole, but watch in awe as The Pride of Alberta roars back and drown the Sharks in oil. Oh yeah, also helped by THAT save from Albert Roloson.

Enjoy!
